def import_data(pth_1, pth_2):
    if os.path.exists(pth_1):
        return pd.read_csv(pth_1, sep=',')
    elif os.path.exists(pth_2):
        return pd.read_csv(pth_2, sep=',')
    else:
        print('  .  ,    .')

def data_view(data):
    #       .    
    data.columns = data.columns. \
                                str.replace(r'([a-z0-9])([A-Z])' , r'\1_\2', regex = True). \
                                str.replace(r'(.)([A-Z][a-z]+)', r'\1_\2', regex = True). \
                                str.replace(r'([a-z0-9])([A-Z])', r'\1_\2', regex = True). \
                                str.replace(r'__([A-Z])', r'_\1', regex = True). \
                                str.replace(r'__([a-z0-9])', r'_\1', regex = True)
    data.columns = data.columns.str.lower()
    print()
    print(color.BLUE + color.BOLD + ' 5  ' + color.END)
    display(data.head()) #   5 
    print()
    print(color.BLUE + color.BOLD + '  ' + color.END)
    print()
    display(data.info()) #    
    print()
    #     .       
    print(color.BLUE + color.BOLD + '    (  )' + color.END)
    display(pd.concat([data.isna().sum().rename('nan_count'), 
                       data.isna().mean().rename('nan_percent'),
                       data.nunique().rename('unique_values')], 
                      axis=1).style.format({'nan_percent' : '{:.2%}'})) 
    print()    
    print(color.BLUE + color.BOLD + '' + color.END)
    print()
    print('  :', data.duplicated().sum())
    print('    : {:.2%}'.format((data.duplicated().sum())/len(data)))
    print()
    print(color.BLUE + color.BOLD + '  , :' + color.END)
    display(data.describe())
    print()    
    #  
    for param in data.columns[1:5]:
        f, (ax_hist, ax_box) = plt.subplots(2, sharex=True, gridspec_kw={"height_ratios": (.85, .15)})
        sns.histplot(data=data, x=param, kde=True, ax=ax_hist)
        sns.boxplot(data=data, x=param, ax=ax_box)
    plt.show()

def len_test(df, train, valid, num):
    print()
    print('   ', num, '== {:.0%}'.format(len(valid)/len(df)))
    print()
    print(color.BLUE + color.BOLD + '      ', num + color.END, '==', len(df))
    print(color.GREEN + color.BOLD + 
          '    ,     =='+ color.END, 
          len(train)+len(valid))

Обучение и проверка модели¶










    3 ,      -  .











In [25]:



     


'''
         :
    
        features_train -  
        target_train -  
        features_valid -   
        target_valid -  
        num - ,        
        
         ,   :
        1.      r2  CV
        2.    RMSE
        3.            
        4.           
    
     :
        1.  
        2.    
        3.      
        4. ,        

'''

def build_model(features_train, target_train, features_valid, target_valid, num):
    model = LinearRegression() #   LinearRegression
    model.fit(features_train, target_train) #     
    predictions_valid = model.predict(features_valid) #      

    #    CV
    folds = KFold(n_splits = 5, shuffle = True, random_state = 42)

    #     -
    scores = cross_val_score(model, features_train, target_train, scoring='r2', cv=folds)
    #  RMSE
    result = mean_squared_error(target_valid, predictions_valid)**.5 #   RMSE   
    #  
    print()
    print(color.BLUE + ' R2   {:.0f}  - =='.format(num) 
          + color.END, scores.mean())
    print(color.BLUE + 'RMSE   {:.0f}    =='.format(num)
          + color.END, result)
    print()
    print(color.BLUE+ 'C     {:.0f} =='.format(num)
          + color.END, predictions_valid.mean())
    
    #          
    result_model = target_valid.reset_index()
    result_model['product_pred'] = predictions_valid
    result_model = result_model.drop(['index'],axis=1)
    
    #  5    
    print('\n')
    print(color.BOLD + '       :' + color.END)
    display(result_model.sample(5))
    display(result_model.describe())
    print()
    
    return model, pd.Series(predictions_valid), target_valid.reset_index(drop=True), result_model

def print_avg_prod(df, num):
    print()
    print('    {:.0f}     :'.format(num), 
          len(df.query('product_pred >= @payback_hole')))
    print('    {:.0f}     : {:.2%}'
          .format(num, (len(df.query('product_pred >= @payback_hole'))/len(df))))
    print()

Расчёт прибыли и рисков¶










 ,   bootstrap        











In [84]:



     


'''
         :
    
        df - ,   
        product_pred -  ,  
        product -  ,   
        num - ,        
        repeat -    bootstrap
        parts -  
        count -   ,    
        
         :
        1.         . .
        2. 95%-     
        3.  2,5%  
        4.   -      

'''

def profit_calc(df, product_pred, product, num, repeat, parts, count):   

    state = np.random.RandomState(42)
    
    values = []
    for i in range(repeat): #  bootstrap    repeat
        selected = (df.sample(random_state=state, n=parts, replace=True) #    parts 
                    .sort_values(product_pred, ascending=False) #      
                    .head(200) #  -200
                   )
        values.append(450e3*selected[product].sum()-10e9) #      -200   
    
    values = pd.Series(values)/10e6 #    . .
    lower = np.percentile(values, 2.5) #  2,5 
    upper = np.percentile(values, 97.5) #  97,5 
    confidence_interval = st.t.interval(0.95, len(values)-1, values.mean(), values.sem()) # 95%  
    mean = values.mean() #   

    f, (ax_hist, ax_box) = plt.subplots(2, sharex=True, gridspec_kw={"height_ratios": (.85, .15)})
    sns.histplot(data=values, kde=True, ax=ax_hist)\
    .set(title=' ,  {}'.format(num),
       ylabel='')
    sns.boxplot(data=values, x=values.values, ax=ax_box)\
    .set(xlabel=' [. .]')
    
    print()
    print(color.BLUE + color.BOLD + '   {}'.format(num) + color.END)
    print('   . .: {:.4f}'.format(mean))
    print('95%-  :', round(lower, 2), '--', round(upper, 2))
    print(' 2,5% : {:.4f}'.format(lower))
    print(' : {:.2%}'.format((values<0).mean()))
    print('--------------------------------------------------------------------------------')
